question:
District category contains Military District, Jewelry District, and Industrial District.
Supermarkets category contains Makro, Tesco, Coles (Australia), and King Soopers.
Product category contains Canned Corn, Ice Cream, and Half-and-half.
The number of each King Soopers 's Canned Corn equals 16.
The number of each Coles (Australia) 's Half-and-half equals the sum of each Industrial District 's Makro, each King Soopers 's Ice Cream, each Coles (Australia) 's Canned Corn, and each Industrial District 's Coles (Australia).
The number of each Industrial District 's Coles (Australia) equals the sum of each Coles (Australia) 's Canned Corn, each King Soopers 's Ice Cream, and each Industrial District 's Makro.
The number of each Makro 's Ice Cream equals 4 times each Makro 's Canned Corn.
The number of each King Soopers 's Ice Cream equals 11.
The number of each Tesco 's Half-and-half equals the sum of each Industrial District 's Coles (Australia), each Military District 's King Soopers, each Makro 's Ice Cream, and each Coles (Australia) 's Canned Corn.
The number of each Military District 's Makro equals the sum of each Makro 's Ice Cream and each Makro 's Canned Corn.
The number of each Tesco 's Canned Corn equals 13.
The number of each Coles (Australia) 's Canned Corn equals 0 times each King Soopers 's Ice Cream.
The number of each Industrial District 's Tesco equals the difference of each Coles (Australia) 's Product and each Tesco 's Canned Corn.
The number of each Makro 's Half-and-half equals 14.
The number of each Jewelry District 's Tesco equals each Industrial District 's Makro.
The number of each Makro 's Canned Corn equals 8.
The number of each Jewelry District 's Makro equals 22 more than each Industrial District 's Makro.
The number of each Industrial District 's Makro equals each King Soopers 's Ice Cream.
The number of each Military District 's King Soopers equals each Makro 's Ice Cream.
How many Makro does Military District have?
solution:
Define each Makro 's Canned Corn as H; So H = 8.
Define each Makro 's Ice Cream as q; So q = 4 * H = 4 * 8 = 9.
Define each Military District 's Makro as T; So T = q + H = 9 + 8 = 17.
